==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Limmer
<hw>Lim"mer</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>limier</ets>. See
<er>Leamer</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A limehound; a
leamer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A mongrel, as a cross between the
mastiff and hound.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A low, base fellow; also, a prostitute.</def>
<mark>[Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thieves, <qex>limmers</qex>, and broken men of the Highlands.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>A man rope at the side of a
ladder.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Limn</ent>⟦br⟧
